  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bacoor Fire NFI Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Assessment team identified the need for kitchen utensils since most of the affected families were not able to save their belongings including kitchenware and eating utensils. This is the top priority for ADRA Response as recommended also by the CSWDO for most of the donations are foods other NFI.
&#x2022;	On 09th April ADRA will send a team for validation of names and to distribute tickets to qualified beneficiaries. A logistics team will also contact the contact volunteers to pack the prepositioned items from the warehouse.
&#x2022;	ADRA has distributed 600 kitchen sets to affected households</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Four hour fire destroyed about 600 homes, displacing around 1,000 families, in a coastal community in Bacoor City in Cavite province on Wednesday night.
&#x2022;	There is one reported fatalities and three children are missing, however the families had to flee their homes leaving behind their belongings to be destroyed in the fire.
&#x2022;	The evacuees are temporarily staying in Maliksi elementary school.
&#x2022;	The duration of how long the people will stay in the evacuation centers is uncertain.</narrative>
  </description>
